                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Back to the original topic...
<br />

<br />
Failing to get some needed help on a final quest in STV (god I hope it's the last in this chain), I joined a couple level 60s ganking their way around.  We didn't corpse camp anyone - cept for a couple level 40s who were camping the GY outside Booty Bay and ganking lowbies.  And we only killed them twice (think they got the message then).
<br />

<br />
It was fun for 30 minutes, and I got bored so went off to Duskwood to farm some herbs and /dance with the lowbie alliance.  I did kill one I saw there since he was a member of CoL (alliance guild that attacks all Horde on sight and frequently ganks in Hillsbrad among other places).  There are 4 guilds I kill on sight on my server - CoL, Arsenal, Grief, and Moon Dancers.  This is simply based on my experience with those guilds (and their posting rhetoric on the realm forum).  I see one, and if I think I have a good chance at them, I kill them.
<br />

<br />
Anyhow I was /waving and /dancing with some alliance and came across a couple pallies.  I /waved and they attacked me.  Both dead in about 20 seconds.  Saw them again a bit later - same thing.  I felt a little bad, but they shouldn't have attacked me.  Maybe they learned something.
<br />

<br />
Why anyone would attack a ?? Rogue is beyond me (esp when they were level 25-29).  Maybe they were RPers.
<br />

<br />
