                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well from ganking point of view I would say that attacking someone which fights a mob is no problem.
<br />
I am a rogue, I sneak backstab and betrail.
<br />

<br />
But I am on a PvE server, so it's a bit different.
<br />
If you are flagged PvP, then you are asking for it.
<br />

<br />
Corpse camping is a no. But there are exceptions.
<br />
e.g. We had a level 55 dorf hunter which attacked crossroads and killed all the quest NPC.
<br />
So all level 20-30 grouped up and killed him.
<br />
He then just resurected and started over again. And again.
<br />
So then we had 2-3 high levels which where there and camped his corpse and forced him to take a res, so he leaves the area.
<br />

<br />
Now this is corpse camping I find ok, since we gave him the chance to go, but he wants to be anoying like hell.
<br />

<br />
As for ganking, the only ganking which happens here is if they force your PvP flag.
<br />
Imagine a rogue with a pvp flag on invis in a newbie zone. Some mage makes an AE to root the mobs he is attacking. The rogue being in the AE range gets hit by it and automatically the mages PvP flag turns on and the rogue can kill him. (Or his friends which are around too).
<br />

<br />
Now that is forcing a PvP flag on someone which doesn't want to PvP. And that is ganking IMO.
<br />

<br />
Iue
<br />
aka
<br />
Grzul 30 Rogue
<br />
